Introduction

Kim Bora, mononymously known as Bora is a South Korean singer under FNC Entertainment and FNC W.. She was a member and the Main Vocalist of the South Korean girl group Cherry Bullet.

On January 21, 2019, she made her official debut as a member of the South Korean girl group Cherry Bullet with the single mini album "Let's Play Cherry Bullet" with "Q & A" serving as the title track.

On July 7, 2021, Bora was confirmed as a contestant on Mnet's survival show, “Girls Planet 999”, along with the other participating trainees, through the prologue trailer. The show began airing on August 6 and ended on October 22. Unfortunately, Bora was eliminated in the finale, with her final rank being K09, and ranking 15th overall.

On May 19, 2023, Bora was confirmed as a constant of Mnet's newest survival show, "Queendom Puzzle". The show began airing on June 13, but Bora was eliminated in the semi-final, her final rank being 20th.
